## ğŸ“¦ Deliverables
<artifacts>
  <![CDATA[
  1. Research report in PDF (structured by blocks).
  2. TAM/SAM/SOM market map with figures calculated and provided in units and in money.
  3. Target audience segments.
  4. JTBD maps per segment. Minimum 3 JTBD scenarios per niche.
  5. Competitor matrix (direct, indirect, alternatives). Competitor map includes at least 4 players
  6. segments that block competitors and Our winning segments
  7. Analyze which parts of the product are ready for use in Kazakhstan right now, without any modifications.
  8. What needs to be modified or created in the product for localization for Kazakhstan (using in-house development).
  9. What needs to be developed or created using third-party solutions or integrations (government portals, data, Smart Bridge, etc.)
  10. Necessary partnership with the government or partners for launch
 11. Bills and other government lobbying efforts required for market entry.
 12. General conclusion: product launch prospects and revenue stream ("quick" or "long" money).
  ]]>
</artifacts>

## ğŸ§ª Methodology
<methodology>
  <![CDATA[
  1. Documentary research: analysis of the Kazakhstan Tax Code, "Digitalization" law, procurement regulations.
  2. Open data analysis: stat.gov.kz, eGov.kz, Ministry of Digital Development, procurement portals.
  3. Competitor analysis and product's website kontur.ru
  4. Qualitative sources: user interviews and reviews, Softline and Directum case studies.
  5. Quantitative analytics: TAM/SAM/SOM, based on enterprises and government structures.
  6. Scenario mapping: JTBD scenarios and needs mapping.
  7. SWOT + risk map: entry points and risk assessment.
  8. Analysis of vendor websites and documentation  
  9. Review of government sources: stat.gov.kz, egov.kz, data.egov.kz, â€œDigital Kazakhstanâ€ publications, uchet.kz  
  10. Collect company, SME and individual entrepreneur data (stat.gov.kz latest releases)  
